Good day Kgotodia and all,

 

Thank you for your email. 

 

Every section within a sectional title scheme has a participation quota
(PQ), which is calculated by expressing the size of each section (floor
area) as a percentage of the total sizes of all sections (% of a whole).

 

Transvalia's 20 sections are all the same size (32 square meters) and so
everyone's PQ values are the same (32 SQM / 640 SQM = 0.0500 PQ).

 

The PQ schedule of a sectional title scheme has three effects:

1.	It determines the size of the undivided share of the common property
the owner of that section owns.
2.	It determines the value of that owner's vote.
3.	It determines the share of the annual levy and other expenses that
owner must pay.

Although, removing water and electricity expenses from your levy and adding
these charges as separate items, will decrease the normal levy amount - you
will find that the total charges on your statements will increase by
approximately 30%.

 

This is the only way we will be able to cover all the scheme's expenses
(council bill, insurance, maintenance, audit, etc.).

 

I hope the above clarifies, but if you have any further queries, please
don't hesitate to contact us. We look forward to your responses to the
highlighted matters.

 

Sincerely,

Nancy




