Dear Trustees,

 

We hope this finds you well. Further to previous communication:

 

Maintenance
Fire safety - Vaal Triangle Fire Services
<http://www.vaaltrianglefireservices.co.za/>  located nearby will provide us
with a quote for any requirements and issue the statutory certificate.
Please confirm who will be the contact person for the inspector to conduct a
survey (would Monday be fine)?

Common Property - Please also advise if there are any maintenance, repair or
replacement needs that we can source quotes for?

 

Financial

Statutory audit - Please advise if there is an auditor you would appoint to
complete the annual financial statements and audit. Alternatively, we can
suggest Certified Master Auditors (CMA <http://www.cmaauditors.co.za> ).

 

Management Report - Please find attached for a detailed analysis of
Transvalia's financial performance as at 31 May 2019. Includes Owner Age
Analysis report of levies outstanding.

 

Budget - Please see attached the estimate budget and proposed levy schedule
for 2020. Monthly municipal charges are based on past billing and we are
investigating the amounts with Emfuleni. We will report back on this
shortly. In the meantime, please would someone be able to provide us with a
copy of your prepaid electricity receipt / advise us on the provider?

 

Arrears

CSOS - After intensively pursuing the CSOS route for owners in arrears since
February, those with conciliation hearings did not attend and so cases were
to go to adjudication. CSOS then informed us that their Adjudication unit is
undergoing transitional changes and the Adjudication process will follow in
due course (up to 2-months). It has become apparent that CSOS is unable to
expeditiously resolve these cases.

 

Legal - No debtors have adhered to their payment arrangements or signed
Acknowledgment of Debt. The decision has therefore been made to hand over
the following units to BBM Law who specialise in arrear levy collections:

*	TV2 (Mphiyakhe) - will not increase payment; balance outstanding
increasing.
*	TV3 (Bahyi) - paid minimal amounts then nothing since Jan; not
responding to contact efforts.
*	TV5 (Fick) - unable to contact; no payments on record.
*	TV9 & TV13 (Motsoagae) - making monthly payments of R750 for each
unit; arrears increasing; not responding to contact efforts.
*	TV15 (Alemeida / Da Silva) - Monthly payments of R2,000 does not
cover levies and charges; needs to increase payment amount; unable to
contact.

In brief, a (registered) Letter of Demand will now be sent / served by the
Sheriff. If no response from the debtors, a formal Summons will be issued
and served again by the Sheriff. If owners do not defend, we will apply for
Default Judgement which vastly affects the creditworthiness of the debtor.
It is at this stage that debtors are most likely to adhere to formal payment
arrangements to avoid Warrants of Execution where movable assets are sold in
auction. However, the final stage would be Section 66 where the property is
sold to recover the debt owed to the BC.

 

We look forward to your feedback and suggestions to address the above
management issues.

 

Kind regards,

Nancy




